</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF91C93EFF62FA66FBEDF955" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF91C93EFF62FA66FBEDF955" blockId="48.[151,1437,1300,2011]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFF62FA66FECCF9C5" bold="true" box="[199,322,1516,1542]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF91C93EFE75FA67FDDDF9C5" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[464,595,1516,1542]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaieteur" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFE75FA67FDDDF9C5" box="[464,595,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">M. kaieteur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFDFEFA66FD41F9C5" bold="true" box="[603,719,1516,1542]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF91C93EFDFEFA66FD41F9C5" box="[603,719,1516,1542]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF91C93EFC0CFA67FB95F9C5" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[937,1051,1517,1542]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaraua" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFC0CFA67FB95F9C5" box="[937,1051,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">M. jaraua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFB86FA66FB19F9C5" bold="true" box="[1059,1175,1516,1542]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF91C93EFB86FA66FB19F9C5" box="[1059,1175,1516,1542]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF91C93EFB02FA66FACBF9C5" box="[1191,1349,1516,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 173–178" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1622,1646]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,571,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-218@47.[160,1428,561,1599]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 173–178. Meri jaraua spec. nov., female. 173–175 ex MNHN 2459, 176–178 IBSP 165050, paratype. 173, 176 epigyne; 174, 177 vulva; 175, 178 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550319/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 173–178</figureCitation>
) by the vulva with internal ducts with FW postero-laterad, GP posteriad and spermathecae ovoid. They are distinguished from the latter species by the epigyne with MS narrow, three times longer than wide, widest posteriorly and EP with anterior margin reaching one fifth MS length (MS roughly two times longer than wide, widest medially and EP with anterior margin reaching half MS lenght in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF91C93EFDDBF9F7FD61F955" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[638,751,1661,1686]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaraua" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFDDBF9F7FD61F955" box="[638,751,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">M. jaraua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFD50F9F6FCE6F955" bold="true" box="[757,872,1660,1686]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF91C93EFD50F9F6FCE6F955" box="[757,872,1660,1686]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF91C93EFF62F92AFAAAF874" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF91C93EFF62F92AFD73F8AD" blockId="48.[151,1437,1300,2011]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFF62F92AFDCBF979" bold="true" box="[199,581,1696,1722]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Description. Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF91C93EFE6FF92AFDB6F979" box="[458,568,1696,1722]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 14.0. Prosoma 6.3 long, 5.8 wide. Opisthosoma 7.3 long, 4.2 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.45, 0.40, 0.26, 0.35; interdistances: 0.35, 0.24, 0.75, 0.69, 0.40, 0.35. Legs: I: 24.9 (7.0, 3.0, 6.5, 6.7, 1.7); II: 26.7 (7.7, 3.1, 7.0, 7.0, 1.4); III: 18.2 (5.2, 2.6, 4.6, 4.4, 1.4); IV: 21.1 (6.5, 2.5, 5.2, 5.3, 1.6). Epigyne: EF wider than long; MAB slightly conspicuous, embedded in EF; EP triangular, opening at posterior margin of MS; LL touching posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF91C93EFD94F8BAFD18F889" box="[561,662,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 184–190" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,344,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-46@49.[152,1434,334,1783]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 184–190. 184–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (184 epigyne, 185 vulva, 186 schematic course of internal duct system); 187–190 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype) left palp (187 prolateral, 188 ventral, 189 retrolateral, 190 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RdP—retro dorsal projection; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550331/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 184</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF91C93EFD07F8BAFD41F889" box="[674,719,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 191–195" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1971,1995]" captionTargetBox="[194,1386,1103,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-374@50.[184,1403,1090,1947]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 191–195. 185–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (191 epigyne, 192 vulva); 193–195 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype), left palp (193 prolateral, 194 ventral, 195 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550334/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">191</figureCitation>
). Vulva: GP 3 times longer than wide, arising from ducts at first turn; SP ovoid; FD antero laterad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF91C93EFDBFF8DEFD39F8AC" box="[538,695,1876,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 184–190" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,344,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-46@49.[152,1434,334,1783]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 184–190. 184–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (184 epigyne, 185 vulva, 186 schematic course of internal duct system); 187–190 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype) left palp (187 prolateral, 188 ventral, 189 retrolateral, 190 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RdP—retro dorsal projection; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550331/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 185–186</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF91C93EFD67F8DEFD7EF8AD" box="[706,752,1876,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 191–195" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1971,1995]" captionTargetBox="[194,1386,1103,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-374@50.[184,1403,1090,1947]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 191–195. 185–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (191 epigyne, 192 vulva); 193–195 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype), left palp (193 prolateral, 194 ventral, 195 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550334/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">192</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF91C93EFF62F8F2FE0AF851" blockId="48.[151,1437,1300,2011]" box="[199,388,1912,1938]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFF62F8F2FE83F851" bold="true" box="[199,269,1912,1938]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Male:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF91C93EFF62F816FAAAF874" blockId="48.[151,1437,1300,2011]" box="[199,1316,1948,1975]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFF62F816FEB1F875" bold="true" box="[199,319,1948,1974]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Variation.</emphasis>
Females (n = 4): total length 10.8–18.0; prosoma length 4.5–6.5; femur I length 5.6–7.8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF91C93EFF62F84AFB2AF818" box="[199,1188,1984,2011]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF91C93EFF62F84AFB2AF818" blockId="48.[151,1437,1300,2011]" box="[199,1188,1984,2011]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF91C93EFF62F84AFEEFF819" bold="true" box="[199,353,1984,2010]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from northern South America (
<collectingCountry id="F3297669FF91C93EFCB9F84AFC01F819" box="[796,911,1984,2010]" name="Venezuela" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3297669FF91C93EFC60F84AFB90F819" box="[965,1054,1984,2010]" name="Guyana" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Guyana</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF91C93EFB90F84AFB19F818" box="[1077,1175,1984,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 315–318" captionStartId="76.[151,264,1371,1395]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,489,1348]" captionTargetId="figure-159@76.[156,1431,489,1348]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES 315–318. Distribution maps for species of Meri gen. nov. 315 (M. martinique spec. nov., M. sanctivincenti (Simon) comb. nov., M. trinitatis (Strand) comb. nov., M. carabobo spec. nov., M. kaieteur spec. nov.); 316 (M. jaraua spec. nov., M. arraijan spec. nov., M. formosus (Banks) comb. nov., M. guri spec. nov., M. tumatumari spec. nov.); 317 (M. zeteki spec. nov., M. manaos spec. nov., M. yaciba spec. nov., M. tapirapeco spec. nov., M. abuna spec. nov.); 318 (M. mathani (Simon) comb. nov., M. pictitarsis (Simon) comb. nov., M. conduri spec. nov., M. paiaia spec. nov., M. tambor spec. nov.);" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550426/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 315</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
